<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>Grind Backend Admin Instructions</title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: #111;
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 40px auto;
    }
    h1, h2 {
      color: #111;
    }
    code, pre {
      background: #f1f1f1;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      padding: 8px;
      display: block;
      white-space: pre-wrap;
    }
    .warning {
      background: #fff3cd;
      border: 1px solid #ffe69c;
      padding: 12px;
      margin: 16px 0;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Grind Website Backend Admin Instructions</h1>

  <p>This document explains exactly how to open the backend admin page for the Grind website.</p>

  <div class="warning">
    <strong>Important:</strong> Do not use VS Code "Go Live" for backend/admin/contact form features. Go Live uses port 5500 or 5501 and only works for static HTML. The backend must be started with <strong>npm start</strong> and opened on port <strong>3000</strong>.
  </div>

  <h2>1. Open The Correct Folder</h2>

  <p>Your project is here:</p>

  <pre>C:\Users\rohtl\Desktop\examdevin\grind-homepage</pre>

  <p>The backend folder is here:</p>

  <pre>C:\Users\rohtl\Desktop\examdevin\grind-homepage\backend</pre>

  <h2>2. Open Terminal</h2>

  <p>You can use Git Bash, PowerShell, VS Code terminal, or Cursor terminal.</p>

  <p>Go to the backend folder:</p>

  <pre>cd ~/desktop/examdevin/grind-homepage/backend</pre>

  <p>If you use PowerShell, you can also write:</p>

  <pre>cd C:\Users\rohtl\Desktop\examdevin\grind-homepage\backend</pre>

  <h2>3. Check Node.js</h2>

  <p>Write this command:</p>

  <pre>node -v</pre>

  <p>If it shows a version number, Node.js is installed.</p>

  <p>If it says command not found, install Node.js from:</p>

  <pre>https://nodejs.org/</pre>

  <h2>4. Create The .env File</h2>

  <p>The backend needs a file named <strong>.env</strong>. This file stores your admin username and password.</p>

  <p>In the backend folder, write:</p>

  <pre>cp .env.example .env</pre>

  <p>If you use PowerShell, write:</p>

  <pre>copy .env.example .env</pre>

  <h2>5. Open The .env File</h2>

  <p>Write this command:</p>

  <pre>notepad .env</pre>

  <p>Inside the file, write this:</p>

  <pre>PORT=3000
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD=kaspar69
SESSION_SECRET=randomsecret123456789</pre>

  <p>Save the file and close Notepad.</p>

  <h2>6. Start The Backend</h2>

  <p>Make sure you are still inside the backend folder:</p>

  <pre>C:\Users\rohtl\Desktop\examdevin\grind-homepage\backend</pre>

  <p>Then write:</p>

  <pre>npm start</pre>

  <p>If it works, you should see:</p>

  <pre>Grind backend töötab: http://localhost:3000
Admin: http://localhost:3000/admin</pre>

  <p>Keep this terminal open. If you close it, the backend stops working.</p>

  <h2>7. Open The Website</h2>

  <p>Open your browser and go to:</p>

  <pre>http://localhost:3000</pre>

  <p>This opens the website through the backend.</p>

  <h2>8. Open The Admin Page</h2>

  <p>Open this link:</p>

  <pre>http://localhost:3000/admin</pre>

  <p>If it asks you to log in, use:</p>

  <pre>Username: admin
Password: kaspar69</pre>

  <h2>9. What You Can Do In Admin</h2>

  <p>Inside the admin page you can:</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Add products</li>
    <li>Edit products</li>
    <li>Delete products</li>
    <li>Read contact form messages</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Contact Form</h2>

  <p>The contact form only works through localhost port 3000.</p>

  <p>Use this link:</p>

  <pre>http://localhost:3000/kontaktivorm.html</pre>

  <p>Do not use this:</p>

  <pre>127.0.0.1:5500
127.0.0.1:5501
file:///C:/Users/...</pre>

  <p>Those are not the backend server, so the form cannot save messages there.</p>

  <h2>11. If It Says Wrong Username Or Password</h2>

  <p>Check these things:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>Make sure the backend is running with <strong>npm start</strong>.</li>
    <li>Make sure you opened <strong>http://localhost:3000/admin</strong>.</li>
    <li>Make sure your <strong>.env</strong> file is inside the backend folder.</li>
    <li>Make sure <strong>ADMIN_USERNAME=admin</strong>.</li>
    <li>Make sure <strong>ADMIN_PASSWORD=kaspar69</strong>.</li>
    <li>If you changed .env, stop the server with <strong>Ctrl + C</strong>, then start again with <strong>npm start</strong>.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>12. If The Contact Form Says Page Does Not Work</h2>

  <p>You are probably using the wrong port.</p>

  <p>Wrong:</p>

  <pre>127.0.0.1:5501/contact</pre>

  <p>Correct:</p>

  <pre>http://localhost:3000/kontaktivorm.html</pre>

  <h2>13. If Port 3000 Is Already In Use</h2>

  <p>Stop the old backend terminal with:</p>

  <pre>Ctrl + C</pre>

  <p>Then start again:</p>

  <pre>npm start</pre>

  <h2>14. Quick Start Commands</h2>

  <p>Use these commands when you want to start the backend:</p>

  <pre>cd ~/desktop/examdevin/grind-homepage/backend
npm start</pre>

  <p>Then open:</p>

  <pre>http://localhost:3000/admin</pre>

  <h2>15. Main Rule</h2>

  <p>Use <strong>localhost:3000</strong> for the backend/admin/contact form.</p>

  <p>Do not use <strong>Go Live</strong> for backend features.</p>
</body>
</html>
